   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422515_1844_05_02_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <salute>
                  <persName>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName>s <choice>
                        <orig>Compts</orig>
                        <reg>Compliments</reg>
                     </choice> to<lb/>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ConoX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Conolly.</persName>
                     <lb/>
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>She believes that <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BaldR1">Baldwin</persName>
               <lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CradC1">Cradock</persName> and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#JoyX1">Joy</persName> are the<lb/>
               booksellers who have <del>the</del>
               <lb/>
               <del>copy</del> all her works except<lb/>
               <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">Helen</title> and the <title ref="./Workography.xml#Memoi1">3<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> edition<lb/>
                  of the Memoirs of R Lovell <choice>
                     <orig>Edge<lb/>
                     worth</orig>
                     <reg>Edgeworth</reg>
                  </choice> Esq</title> which 2 works are<lb/>
               published by <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BentR1">Bentley</persName>.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss <choice><orig>E</orig><reg>Edgeworth</reg></choice></persName> long ago sold the<lb/>
               copy right of all but <title ref="./Workography.xml#Helen1">Helen</title>
               <lb/>
               &amp; those mem<hi rend="superscript">s</hi>. - She has no<lb/>
               <del>concern with or</del> knowledge<lb/>
               of how or by whom they are<lb/>
               now published -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>She thanks <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ConoX1">
                  <hi rend="superscript">Mr</hi>. Conolly</persName> for<lb/>
               his good opinion of the tendency<lb/>
               of her books &amp; is sorry she can<lb/>
               not give him better information<lb/>
            </p>
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422515_1844_05_02_page01.jpg"/>
            <p>She believes the American<lb/>
               <choice><orig>Ed<hi rend="superscript">n</hi>.</orig><reg>Education</reg></choice> is the most full and<lb/>
               perfect of <add>all</add> her own &amp; her<lb/>
               fathers works - including<lb/>
               <title ref="./Workography.xml#Pract1">Practical Education</title> &amp;<lb/>
               <title ref="./Workography.xml#Early1">Early Lessons</title>
               <lb/>
            </p>
